      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_85",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "5.  (1)  Every  statutory  body  shall  keep  or  shall  cause  to  be  kept \nproper  accounts  and  other  records  in  respect  of  its  operations  in \naccordance  with  generally  accepted  accounting  principles  and  shall \ncause  to  be  prepared  a  statement  of  its  accounts  in  respect  of  each \nfinancial year and shall, within six month after the end of that financial \nyear  or  such  extension  thereof  as  may  be  granted  under  section  9, \nsubmit the same to the Auditor General for audit.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_86",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(2)  The  Auditor  General  shall  forthwith  cause  the  statement  of",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_87",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "accounts to be audited.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_88",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Provisions of Audit Act 1957 to apply",
