      "heading": "PART IV",
      "content": "PART IV",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_91",
      "heading": "SUBMISSION AND TABLING OF ACCOUNTS AND ANNUAL \nREPORTS",
      "content": "SUBMISSION AND TABLING OF ACCOUNTS AND ANNUAL \nREPORTS",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_92",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Time limit for submission of audited statement of accounts, etc., to \nMinister",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_93",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "7.  Every  statutory  body  shall,  in  respect  of  each  financial  year  and \nwithin one month after the receipt of its audited statement of accounts \nand the Auditor General’s report thereon, if  any, submit the same to \nthe Minister together with a report of its activities.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_94",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "8                                     Laws of Malaysia                            ACT 240",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_95",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Minister to cause audited statement of accounts, etc., to be tabled  \nin Parliament",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_96",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "8.  The Minister shall, as soon as may be practicable on receipt of the \naudited statement of accounts, the Auditor General’s report thereon, if \nany, and the report of the activities of a statutory body, cause the same \nto be laid on the table of each House of Parliament.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_97",
      "heading": "PART V",
      "content": "PART V",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_98",
      "heading": "EXTENSION OF TIME LIMIT",
      "content": "EXTENSION OF TIME LIMIT",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_99",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Application for, and grant of, extension of time limit",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_100",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "9.  (1)  Where  a  statutory  body  is  unable  to  submit  its  statement  of \naccounts for audit within six months after the end of the financial year \nto  which  the  accounts relate,  it  shall,  before  the  expiry  of  such  time \nlimit, apply in writing to the Minister for an extension thereof and shall \nalso set out the reasons for applying for such extension.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_101",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(2)  Where  a  statutory  body  applies  under  subsection  (1)  for  an \nextension of the time limit of six months, the Minister, if satisfied with \nthe  reasons  for  the  application,  may,  with  the  concurrence  of  the \nMinister of Finance, grant such extension of the time limit as may be \ndeemed  necessary  but such extension shall  not in any case exceed a \nperiod  of  three  months  in  the  aggregate  in  respect  of  each  financial \nyear, and the statutory body shall then submit its statement of accounts \nfor audit within the time limit as extended.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_102",
      "heading": "PART VI",
      "content": "PART VI",
      "section_number": null,
